'''Arastasia''' was the daughter of an [[unnamed lord]]. A farm hand from her father's farm, [[Dentristus]] loved her.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=His lord had a beautiful daughter, Arastasia, with whom he was in love}} During a harsh winter, the [[Wintertodt]] was drawn from the north devouring animals and crops,{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=That winter was the Great Winter which drew down the Wintertodt from the north, It proceeded to devour the animals upon the farm and freezing the next year's crops.}} which caused Arastasia to weep at the fear and distress caused to her people.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=The lord had no food and Arastasia wept at the fear and distress caused to her people.}} Dentristus vowed to defeat the [[Wintertodt]], and in exchange the lord offered Arastasia's hand in marriage.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=I vow that I will venture into the mountains and destroy the beast so it shall trouble us no more....

...if you succeed I will grant you my daughter's hand in marriage as you will truly be the only man that can make her happy.}} Though this would never come to pass as Dentristus was defeated.{{CiteNPC|npc=Wintertodt parable|quote=Dentristus lay dead before he even saw the Wintertodt}}

